# Implementation Plan - Liquid Ether Fluid Simulation

Build a production-grade, ultra-high-quality fluid simulation background for a Flutter mobile app using custom GLSL shaders and multi-touch integration.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Shader Compilation**: Requires Flutter 3.7+. The shaders will be registered in `pubspec.yaml` and compiled by Flutter's asset packager using the Impeller/Skia compiler.
> - **Uniform Layout Order**: The sequence of calling `FragmentShader.setFloat` in Dart must match the exact declaration order in `fluid.frag`.
> - **Compatibility**: Tested on Android (Skia/Vulkan) and iOS (Impeller/Metal).

## Proposed Changes

We will create the following files to implement the simulation:

---

### Shaders Component

#### [NEW] [fluid_utils.glsl](file:///d:/flutter_projects/lib/shaders/fluid_utils.glsl)
Contains noise, hash, and Fractional Brownian Motion (fBm) helper functions:
- 2D Value/Gradient noise.
- 8-octave fBm with rotational matrices per octave to avoid axis-aligned artifacts.
- Dual-compilation guard for when compiled standalone.

#### [NEW] [fluid.frag](file:///d:/flutter_projects/lib/shaders/fluid.frag)
The main GLSL fragment shader:
- Defines the 3-level domain warping equations.
- Handles up to 5 multi-touch coordinates and calculates pressure disturbances.
- Defines the custom Deep Space purple/indigo color palette.
- Combines 3 luminous glow passes.
- Applies vignette, chromatic aberration, film grain, and gamma correction post-processing.

---

### Dart Flutter Widgets Component

#### [NEW] [touch_point.dart](file:///d:/flutter_projects/lib/widgets/touch_point.dart)
The data model for tracking a pointer's position, strength, and velocity. Implements frame-rate-independent decay.

#### [NEW] [liquid_ether_painter.dart](file:///d:/flutter_projects/lib/widgets/liquid_ether_painter.dart)
Implements `CustomPainter` to bind Flutter values to the compiled `FragmentShader` uniforms:
- Feeds `uTime`, `uResolution`, `uTouches`, `uTouchStrengths`, `uTouchCount`, `uFlowSpeed`, `uTurbulence`, and `uGlowIntensity`.
- Ensures zero allocations inside the `paint` call (reusing Paint, Rect, and cached float lists).

#### [NEW] [liquid_ether.dart](file:///d:/flutter_projects/lib/widgets/liquid_ether.dart)
The main stateful widget holding the simulation state:
- Manages the shader lifecycle (loading the shader from assets).
- Listens to raw pointer events using `Listener` for raw multi-touch support.
- Runs a Ticker loop tracking real delta-time to decay touches and drive the time uniform.
- Optimizes widget updates using `RepaintBoundary`.

---

